  "issue_number": 944,
  "issue_title": "New API endpoint consistency",
  "issue_body": "Codex implemented the following PR 918 review fixes for API consistency and testing split.  Would be great to create an LLM prompt that runs after every API endpoint comit:\n\n- Added\u00a0**Minitest-only behavioral coverage**\u00a0for new API endpoints:\n    - [holdings_controller_test.rb (line 5)](app://-/index.html# \"/Users/jjmata/src/Codex/we-promise/sure/test/controllers/api/v1/holdings_controller_test.rb (line 5)\")\n    - [trades_controller_test.rb (line 5)](app://-/index.html# \"/Users/jjmata/src/Codex/we-promise/sure/test/controllers/api/v1/trades_controller_test.rb (line 5)\")\n- Kept rswag as docs-only (no\u00a0expect/assert\u00a0blocks in\u00a0spec/requests/api/v1).\n- Fixed one docs consistency issue:\u00a0valuations\u00a0rswag now uses the same API key auth pattern as other API docs:\n    - [valuations_spec.rb (line 23)](app://-/index.html# \"/Users/jjmata/src/Codex/we-promise/sure/spec/requests/api/v1/valuations_spec.rb (line 23)\")\n\nWhat\u2019s covered in Minitest now:\n\n- holdings: index/show, read-only access, filtering, invalid date\u00a0422, missing auth\u00a0401.\n- trades: index/show/create/update/destroy, read-only write-blocking (403), account capability checks, invalid inputs, invalid date\u00a0422, not found\u00a0404, missing auth\u00a0401.",
  "merged_at": "2026-02-10T22:36:25.000Z",
